name: Middle of linked list
sourceCode: export function findMiddle(list) { let fast = list.head; let slow = list.head; while (fast && fast.next) { fast = fast?.next?.next; slow = slow?.next; } return slow; }

name: Largest element in array
sourceCode: export function largestItem(arr) { let max = arr[0]; for (let i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) { if (arr[i] > max) { max = arr[i]; } } return max; }

name: Deletion in array
sourceCode: export function deleteItem(arr, k) { for (let i = k; i < arr.length - 1; i++) { arr[i] = arr[i + 1]; } arr.length--; }

name: Array binary search
description: Binary search is an efficient algorithm for finding the position of a target value within a sorted array. It works by repeatedly dividing the search interval in half, which makes it much faster than linear search, especially for large datasets.
sourceCode: export function binarySearch(arr, x) { let low = 0; let high = arr.length - 1; while (high >= low) { const mid = low + Math.floor((high - low) / 2); if (arr[mid] === x) { return mid; } if (arr[mid] > x) { high = mid - 1; } else { low = mid + 1; } } return -1; }

name: Segregate 0s and 1s in array (two pointers method)
description: You are given an array of 0s and 1s in random order. Segregate 0s on left side and 1s on right side of the array
sourceCode: export function segregate0and1(arr) { let left = 0; let right = arr.length - 1; while (left < right) { // Increment left index while we see 0 at left while (arr[left] === 0 && left < right) { left++; } // Decrement right index while we see 1 at right while (arr[right] === 1 && left < right) { right--; } // If left is smaller than right then there is a 1 at left // and a 0 at right so we exchange arr[left] and arr[right] if (left < right) { arr[left] = 0; arr[right] = 1; left++; right--; } } }

name: Reverse array - two pointers approach
description: Given an array of integers the task is to move all the zeros to the end of the array while maintaining the relative order of all non-zero elements.
sourceCode: export function reverseArray(arr) { let left = 0; let right = arr.length - 1; while (left < right) { // Swap the elements at left and right position [arr[left], arr[right]] = [arr[right], arr[left]]; left++; right--; } }

name: Reverse array - naive approach
description: Given an array of integers the task is to move all the zeros to the end of the array while maintaining the relative order of all non-zero elements.
sourceCode: export function reverseArray(arr) { let n = arr.length; let temp = new Array(n); // Copy elements from original array to temp in reverse order for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) { temp[i] = arr[n - i - 1]; } // Copy elements back to original array for (let k = 0; k < n; k++) { arr[k] = temp[k]; } }

name: Reverse array - by swapping elements
description: Given an array of integers the task is to move all the zeros to the end of the array while maintaining the relative order of all non-zero elements.
sourceCode: export function reverseArray(arr) { let n = arr.length; let x; for (let i = 0; i < n / 2; i++) { x = n - i - 1; [arr[i], arr[x]] = [arr[x], arr[i]]; } }

name: Move all zeros to end of array (naive method)
description: Given an array of integers the task is to move all the zeros to the end of the array while maintaining the relative order of all non-zero elements.
sourceCode: export function pushZerosToEnd(arr) { const n = arr.length; const temp = new Array(n); // to keep track of the index in temp[] let j = 0; // Copy non-zero elements to temp[] for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) { if (arr[i] !== 0) { temp[j] = arr[i]; j++; } } // Fill remaining positions in temp[] with zeros while (j < n) { temp[j] = 0; j++; } // Copy all the elements from temp[] to arr[] for (let k = 0; k < n; k++) { arr[k] = temp[k]; } }

name: Move all zeros to end of array (best method)
description: Given an array of integers the task is to move all the zeros to the end of the array while maintaining the relative order of all non-zero elements.
sourceCode: export function pushZerosToEnd(arr) { // Pointer to track the position for next non-zero element let count = 0; for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) { if (arr[i] !== 0) { // Swap the current element with the 0 at index 'count' [arr[i], arr[count]] = [arr[count], arr[i]]; count++; } } }
